---

Trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length
of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Thinly slice the @portobello mushrooms{3}. Halve the @mangetout{80%grams} widthways.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh
out onto a #board{}, face-down. Slice into 1cm thick slices.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
#lid{}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%grams} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and
@sugar{1%tsp} for pickling. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then add the carrot
ribbons.

Mix together well, then set aside to pickle.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the sliced portobellos to the pan, then stir-fry until softened,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the mushrooms have softened, add the mangetout. Stir-fry for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @gochujang paste{50%grams}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @honey{15%grams} and
@water{50%ml} for the sauce, then stir to combine.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Simmer, stirring frequently, until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, pour the pickling liquid from the carrot ribbons into the
rice and stir together. Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your
#serving bowls{}.

Top your rice with the gochujang mushrooms and mangetout (including any sauce from
the pan), pickled carrot ribbons and sliced avocado in separate sections.

Drizzle the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and sprinkle the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%grams}
over everything to finish.

Enjoy!